About the Fraud:\par
\fs24\tab On June 15th, 2022, Haldiram's, one of India's largest snack and sweets manufacturer, was hit by a ransomware attack. The attackers demanded $7.5 million in Bitcoin as ransom to restore access to the company's servers and data.\par
\par
\tab The ransomware attack affected the entire IT system of the company, including its servers, applications, and databases. The attackers were able to encrypt all the company's data, making it impossible for the employees to access it. The hackers also claimed to have stolen sensitive data from the company's servers, including customer information and financial records.\par
\par
\tab Haldiram's IT team immediately shut down the affected systems and disconnected them from the network to prevent further damage. The company then contacted law enforcement agencies and cybersecurity experts to investigate the attack and restore its systems.\par
\par
\tab The investigation revealed that the attackers used a variant of the Ryuk ransomware to launch the attack. They gained access to the company's network through a phishing email sent to an employee. The email contained a malicious attachment that, when opened, installed the ransomware on the employee's computer, which then spread across the network.\par
\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa200\sl360\slmult1\qc 6\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa200\sl360\slmult1\tab Haldiram's decided not to pay the ransom and instead restored its systems from backups. The company also strengthened its cybersecurity measures, including employee training on identifying phishing emails and the installation of advanced security software.\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa200\sl360\slmult1\qc\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa200\sl360\slmult1\fs28 Laws implemented on the Attacker:\par
\fs24\tab The attackers behind the ransomware attack on Haldiram's will face severe legal consequences if apprehended. The following laws will be implemented against them:\par
\par
\tab The Indian Penal Code: The attackers will be charged with various offenses under the Indian Penal Code, including theft, extortion, and criminal conspiracy.\par
\par
\tab The Information Technology Act, 2000: The attackers will also face charges under the Information Technology Act, 2000, which includes provisions related to unauthorized access to computer systems, data theft, and cyberstalking.\par
\par
\tab The Prevention of Money Laundering Act, 2002: If the attackers are found to have received the ransom amount in Bitcoin, they will also face charges under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act, 2002, which prohibits money laundering activities.\par
\fs28\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa200\sl360\slmult1\qc 7\par

\pard\widctlpar\sa200\sl360\slmult1 Conclusion:\par
\fs24\tab The ransomware attack on Haldiram's highlights the importance of strong cybersecurity measures and employee training to prevent such attacks. It also underscores the severity of cybercrime and the need for strict legal action against the perpetrators. Businesses should take proactive measures to protect their networks and data, including regular backups, advanced security software, and employee training on cybersecurity best practices.\par

